Section 1:
Act 136 of the Regular Session
1 State of Arkansas As Engrossed: H2/10/25
A Bill
2 95th General Assembly
3 Regular Session, 2025 HOUSE BILL 1287
4
5 By: Representative L. Johnson
6 By: Senator Irvin
7
For An Act To Be Entitled
8
9 AN ACT TO AMEND THE HEALTHCARE CONTRACTING
10 SIMPLIFICATION ACT; TO DEFINE "DOWNCODE" UNDER THE
11 HEALTHCARE CONTRACTING SIMPLIFICATION ACT; TO REQUIRE
12 NOTIFICATION BY CONTRACTING ENTITIES OF DOWNCODING
13 CERTAIN HEALTHCARE SERVICES; AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES.
14
15
Subtitle
16
17 TO AMEND THE HEALTHCARE CONTRACTING
18 SIMPLIFICATION ACT; TO DEFINE "DOWNCODE"
19 UNDER THE HEALTHCARE CONTRACTING
20 SIMPLIFICATION ACT; AND TO REQUIRE
21 NOTIFICATION BY CONTRACTING ENTITIES OF
22 DOWNCODING.
23
24 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF ARKANSAS:
25
26 SECTION 1. Arkansas Code ยง 23-99-1202, concerning definitions used
27 under the Healthcare Contracting Simplification Act, is amended to add an
28 additional subdivision to read as follows:
29 (14) "Downcode" means to change a claim to a lower-cost
30 healthcare service than what was contained in the original claim that a
31 healthcare provider submitted or billed to a contracting entity.
32
33 SECTION 2. Arkansas Code Title 23, Chapter 99, Subchapter 12, is
34 amended to add an additional section to read as follows:
35 23-99-1211. Notice required for downcode of claim.
36 A contracting entity that downcodes a claim submitted by a healthcare
*ANS040*
